'''Amin Maktab''', established in 1961,<ref name=shaukat>{{cite web|url=http://tribune.com.pk/story/443566/dealing-with-disabilities-focus-on-what-they-can-do-not-what-they-cant/|title=Dealing with disabilities: ‘Focus on what they can do, not what they can’t’|publisher=[[PakTribune]]|location=[[Lahore]]|first=Aroosa|last=Shaukat|date=September 28, 2012|work=tribune.com}}</ref> is a [[special education]] center for mentally challenged children located in [[Gulberg, Lahore|Gulberg]], [[Lahore]], [[Punjab (Pakistan)|Punjab]], [[Pakistan]]. Amin Maktab is the oldest institution in Lahore for intellectually challenged children.<ref name=shaukat/>
==History== Amin Maktab School was established in small rented building in October 1961 by the Pakistan Society for the Welfare of Retarded Children.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dawn.com/2012/02/27/mainstreaming-the-mentally-challenged/|title=Mainstreaming the mentally challenged|publisher=[[Dawn News]]|location=[[Lahore]]|first=Mansoor|last=Malik|date=February 27, 2012|work=dawn.com}}</ref> In 1987, a multi-purpose campus in J-block of [[Gulberg, Lahore|Gulberg]] was built by the local architect Fuad Ali Butt.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://archnet.org/library/sites/one-site.jsp?site_id=1010 |title=Amin Maktab School |work=archnet.org |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121217002642/http://archnet.org/library/sites/one-site.jsp?site_id=1010 |archivedate=2012-12-17 }}</ref> In 1991, an outreach programme was started, with the aid from [[UNICEF]], for the purpose of spreading awareness as well as providing services and training to the homes of mentally challenged children in economically depressed areas of Lahore.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://srdw.net/srdw/amin-maktab-outreach-programme-campus-lahore/|title=Amin Maktab – Outreach Programme Campus Lahore|year=2011|work=srdw.net}}</ref> Currently, the management of Amin Maktab is handled by now retired Justice Aamer Raza Khan.
