{{Infobox person | name = Otto Aron Salomon | image =SalomonOtto.jpg | image_size = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = 1849 | birth_place = [[Gothenburg, Sweden]] | death_date = 1907 | death_place = | death_cause = | residence = | other_names =Otto Salomon | known_for = | education = | employer = | occupation = | title = | salary = | networth = | height = | weight = | term = | predecessor = | successor = | party = | boards = | religion = | spouse = | partner = | children = | parents = | relatives = | signature = | website = | footnotes = | nationality = Swedish }}
'''Otto Aron Salomon''' (1849-1907) was a Swedish educator and both a noted writer and proponent of educational [[sloyd]]. Born in [[Gothenburg, Sweden]] in 1849, Salomon studied at the Institute of Technology in Stockholm but left after a year to accept a position as Director of the Sloyd Teachers Seminary in Naas, Sweden. It was while at the seminary that Salomon was able to popularize the educational sloyd movement.
